law.catch_line: Date of approval or passage to be stated at end of act.
law.text: The date of the approval of an act by the Governor, or the day it passes against his objections, shall be stated at the end of the act.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 2420.
